parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The dim or inadequate headlights can cause a visibility hazard, making it difficult or impossible to drive safely at night, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The headlights are extremely dim
the low beam headlights are not illuminating sufficiently
the headlights are fogging up inside
the reflective coating is burning due to the temperature of the halogen headlights
the headlights are not providing adequate illumination for safe driving
the driver has to use high beams to see the road
the headlights are almost non-existent
the vehicle cannot be driven safely at night.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause loss of power, hesitation, or slipping, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or slips when accelerating
loses power
or fails to shift gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
or the vehicle stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle or all-wheel drive system can cause loss of traction, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle displays warning messages related to the rear axle or all-wheel drive system
or the vehicle loses traction or power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs or even engine failure.
symptoms: The vehicle's timing chain is damaged
causing engine noise or failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, leading to accidents or difficulty driving at night.
symptoms: The headlights are dim or cloudy
reducing visibility.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of electrical systems can cause various issues, including loss of power, warning lights, or even engine failure.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences electrical issues
such as warning lights
loss of power
or strange noises.
